<p>A long-standing policy on protest guidelines was changed in a closed-door meeting on April 24, less than 24 hours before the start of a scheduled protest. The policy change was used to justify the presence of state police on IU Bloomingtonâ€™s campus and the arrest of more than 50 students and faculty on April 25 and 27. Year-long bans were meted out to those arrested. <a href="content/policepresence.html">Read moreâ€¦</a></p>

